data.value: This plugin checks wether the subtitle is based on text (SRT), image (SUB) or is already integrated into the movie. If this fails for image based subtitles, then the subtitles appear twice on the screen. Settings this flag can fix this, but then movies with text based subtitles might be displayed wrong.

data.name: label41.Text
data.value: Especially for fast moving objects a lot of errors occur, as the 3D is generated by the difference between to frames. Therefore faster moving objects have more depth which sometimes leads to very strange results.

data.name: label44.Text
data.value: If the TV or Beamer has an IP Address, a Ping will be used to determine if the device is on or off, before sending any command. In case of IR commands this avoids problems with IR devices, because all remotes use the same IR code for Power on/off. If we send the Power IR command to a device that is already off, we will turn it on instead, which was not intended.
